i Tankage & piping project of UAE And CCC Tankage Project at Khazzan , Oman. 2. Worked with “PT IOT EPC Indonesia (Deputation From Parent Company – IOT Anwesha Engineering & Construction Ltd), Karimun, Indonesia as Dy.Manager Accounts & Admin (Project) from Feb 2014 to December 2015 at their “Tankage Project (Project Value – USD 76,00,000) ”, PT Oiltanking , Karimun, Indonesia. 3. Worked with “PT IOT EPC Indonesia (Deputation From Parent Company – IOT Anwesha Engineering & Construction Ltd), Karimun, Indonesia as Dy.Manager - Accounts & Admin (Project) from Jan 2016 to July 2016 at their “Piping Project (Project Value – USD 46,00,000) ”, PT Oiltanking , Karimun, Indonesia. Engaged as Accounts & Administration In Charge at our various India EPC Project 4. Worked with “M/S IOT Anwesha Engineering & Construction Ltd” Vadodara, Gujarat as a Accounts & Admin Officer (Project) from August 2013 to November 2013 at their “Civil & Tankage Project (Project Value – INR 37 Cr.) ”, IOCL , Khunti, Ranchi, Jharkhand. 5. Worked with “M/S IOT Anwesha Engineering & Construction Ltd” Vadodara, Gujarat as a Accounts & Admin Officer (Project) from May 2012 to July – 2013 at their “Civil & Structural Work For Edible Oil Refinery Expansion Project (Project Value – INR 35 Cr.) ”, Adani Wilmar Ltd, Mundra, Kutch, Gujarat. 6. Worked with “M/S IOT Anwesha Engineering & Construction Ltd ”Vadodara, Gujarat as a Finance & Admin Officer (Project) from January 2011 to May 2012 at their “Balance Combined Piping & Structure Project (Project Value – INR 30 Cr.)”,IOCL- Vadinar ,Jamnagar , Gujarat. 7. Worked with “M/S IOT Anwesha Engineering & Construction Ltd”, Vadodara,Gujarat as a Jr. Accounts & Admin Officer (Project) from March 2010 to December 2010 at their “Crude Oil & Fire Water Tankage Project (Project Value – INR 37 Cr.) ”, IOCL – Vadinar, Jamnagar, Gujarat. 8. Worked With “M/S IOT Anwesha Engineering & Construction Ltd”, Vadodara, Gujarat as a Jr. Accounts & Admin Officer from December 2008 to February 2010 at Head Office (Vadodara). PRESENT JOB PROFILE (Accounts & Administration) My designation of Accounts & Administration Manager is a Middle Management position within our Company Organization. At our head office – Vadodara, India, I functionally Report to Shareholder Of The Company ,Vadodara & have following Functions under my preview as below FINANCE & ACCOUNTS FUNCTION’S PORTFOLIOS  Cash & bank function (Assisted by 2 Talented Subordinates)  Project site fund management & reporting  Account payable management & payroll accounting  Cost Statement Preparation for project cost accounting & financial ledger reconciliation, monthly project accounting & trail balance reporting  MIS reporting for site management review meetings  Client collection & revenue reconciliation  Asset & inventory accounting  WIP calculation based on PUC/POC method for INDIAN GAAP  Working capital arrangement with local banks for our various projects ADMINISTRATION FUNCTION’S PORTFOLIOS  Responsible for Compilation of MIS reports of all project sites, Head office, Regional office for preparation of board data which is required every month for board of directors meeting, reporting to Head- corporate Affairs, Human Resource & Administration.  Responsible for the Implementation of company policy for all staff & workmen at all level. Also independent charge for preparation of site handbook/guidelines for disbursement to the project managers and site HR/Admin representative for implementation under reporting to myself.  Responsible for the Payroll process for entire organization, Reimbursement to the various levels of officials, Month wise reports, Tracking Attendance and up to disbursement level with a team of payroll process. Attendance report of Head office, Project sites, Regional office thus matching data with payroll.  Responsible for the Documentation for creating personnel files of each and every staff & workmen keeping all records with checklist on each files, which is done through a team of documentation officers at head office as well as branch office.  Responsible for the implementation and monitoring of statutory compliance of the organization centrally at head office, viz. Employee Provident Fund (EPF), ESIC, Workmen compensation policies, Medical insurance, Group personnel accident policies & their renewal process.  Responsible for Full & Final settlement of Exiting employees by developing smooth exit clearance and exit interview process, thus making people comfortable even at the time of exit from the organization. Also completion of the Gratuity process in case of long associated employees. ADDITIONAL FUNCTION’S PORTFOLIOS Handling international shipment & logistic related all activity from India to UAE, OMAN for project materials shipment purpose as per our company project requirement. ACHIEVEMENT: Two Consecutive Years (2012-2013) awarded as “Best Performance – Accounts & Administration” in M/S IOT Anwesha Engineering & Construction Ltd. | MIS | 2019-2019"}]'::jsonb, '[]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\Ashis Karfa.pdf', 'Name: Administration Professional

